Hestia is a lesser deity of the Olympian pantheon. She is the oldest child of Cronus and Rhea, the goddess of family, hearth, and home. She is neutral good.
She dwells with most of the rest of her family in Olympus.
Sources: Deities &amp; Demigods (Third Edition), Dragon magazine #153 - "Following in Their Footsteps", Dragon magazine #283 - "Do-It-Yourself Deities"